  "text": "Bladder icc-lcs are deemed to control the spontaneous contractions of detrusor smooth muscle [CITATION_1] . Thus, in our study, corresponding to the decreased bladder icc-lc excitability, we found that detrusor strips in Sci rats generated much weaker spontaneous phasic contractions than that in normal and sham rats. We further detected that the tolerance of detrusor strips to Zd7288 were decreased in Sci rats. these results could also be attributed to the decreased Hcn channel expression and function. accordingly, we conclude that Hcn channels can control the spontaneous contraction of detrusor strips via regulating bladder icc-lc excitability, and correspondingly, altered Hcn channel expression and function in pathologic conditions may lead to disordered detrusor strip contractility by damaging the bladder icc-lc function.",
